==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sudatory
<hw>Su"da*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sudatorius</ets>, fr. <ets>sudare</ets> to sweat: cf. F.
<ets>sudatoire</ets>. See <er>Sweat</er>.]</ety> <def>Sweating;
perspiring.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sudatory</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sudatory
<hw>Su"da*to*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Sudatories</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>sudatorium</ets>.]</ety> <def>A bagnio; a sweating bath; a vapor
bath.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These <qex>sudatories</qex> are much in request for many
infirmities.</q> <rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sudd</ent>⟦br⟧
